race.comment: STREET LEGAL (2) resumes having run a strong race in metro 2yo company at Sandown Hillside on debut before a spell, beaten a long neck in a good performance. He's been given time and jumped out well enough for this. Should kick up from the inside gate and take catching. EDEN ROSE (6) ran some cracking races as a 2yo, resuming this season with a solid third at Moonee Valley over 1200m. Back in trip for this is some niggle but she'll be charging late. CONFLICT (1) is a gelding by Russian Revolution on debut for the Moody & Coleman yard. He's been jumping out well and can figure. ANGEL IN BLACK (3) is a Shamus Award filly on debut who has won a trial and warrants respect.
